    <p class="sub">A few arguments, not a feed. The thinking behind the work.</p>
  </div></section>
  <section><div class="wrap">
    <div class="pillar"><h3>AI is an organizational problem, not a model problem.</h3><p class="muted">AI already delivers insight, decision support, and autonomy. The challenge is no longer whether the capability exists, but whether organizations can use it: successful adoption is an organizational problem, not a model problem. <em>(essay — coming)</em></p></div>
    <div class="pillar"><h3>From cybersecurity to cyber-power.</h3><p class="muted">National advantage doesn't come from defense alone; it comes from how a country turns innovation and organization into strategic capability. The argument behind the book and the NATO work. <em>(essay — coming)</em></p></div>
    <div class="pillar"><h3>Capacity that outlasts the report.</h3><p class="muted">Why durable national cyber capability has to be built as a complex socio-technical-economic system — the method behind the World Bank roadmaps. <em>(essay — coming)</em></p></div>
  </div></section>
